Implemented and committed `noscope-7r6` with strict TDD flow.

- I added NS-047 rollback-budget wiring in `src/main.rs`: mint failure in `cmd_run` now catches `CredentialSetError::MintFailed`, revokes succeeded tokens with budgeted retries, then returns a mint-failure error.
- New rollback logic is implemented via `revoke_token_with_budget` and `revoke_run_credentials` in `src/main.rs`, with:
  - wall-clock budget enforcement using `RollbackBudget.revoke_timeout`
  - exponential backoff (`100ms`, `200ms`, `400ms`, ...)
  - per-attempt logging through `RollbackLogEntry`
  - `budget=0` behavior that disables retry execution
- I added dedicated NS-047 tests in `src/main.rs` (`rollback_budget_wiring_tests`) for:
  - retrying failed revocations
  - wall-clock cap behavior
  - exponential backoff progression
  - per-attempt rollback logging format
  - zero-budget disable behavior
  - timed-out attempt logging
- Provenance draft was written to `./.beads/provenance-drafts/noscope-7r6.md`.

Verification run:
- `cargo test` (red first, then green)
- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` (clean)

Linus-style self-review (and fixes applied):
- Called out missing attempt-time budget enforcement; fixed by wrapping each revoke attempt in `tokio::time::timeout(remaining_budget, ...)`.
- Called out magic-number backoff; fixed by introducing a named constant in `rollback_backoff_for_retry`.
- Added extra edge-case test for timed-out attempts.

Commit created (not pushed):
- `fc8a2a6`
- `feat: wire rollback budget into run revocation path (noscope-7r6)`
